    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, i see what you're saying about it needing to be relevant, but if we just let judges interpret it based on \"societal changes,\" isn't that basically just saying the Constitution doesn't actually have a fixed meaning anymore? like, if the meaning is always shifting, isn't the living constitution approach just a way to legitimize whatever political agenda a certain group of judges has at the time?",
