      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The core danger of the \"living constitution\" is precisely that it grants judges unfettered power to impose their contemporary political will as law. If the meaning is perpetually shifting based on the current cultural climate, the Constitution ceases to be a stable legal document and becomes a malleable political tool. This dynamic allows judges to effectively legislate from the bench, which is the very definition of judicial overreach that originalists seek to prevent.",
